  <data key="d6">edge.concept.constancy_fortitude.part_of.concept.patience</data>
  <data key="d7">afflicteth the soul ." Hence there may be patience in bearing this trial, as in enduring any other sorrows. Accordingly longanimity and constancy are both comprised under patience, in so far as both the delay of the hoped for good (which regards longanimity) and the toil which man endures in persistently accomplishing a good work (which regards constancy) m</data>
