  <data key="d7">praise because thereby a man does not forsake a good on account of long endurance of difficulties and toils: and it is directly opposed to this, seemingly, for a man to be ready to forsake a good on account of difficulties which he cannot endure. This is what we understand by effeminacy, because a thing is said to | The Philosopher says (Ethic. vii, 7) that "the persevering man is opposed to the effeminate."</data>
  <data key="d20">opposed_vice | perseverance</data>
